monogr.title: Edward T. Newell notebook on coins of Amphipolis, undated

abstract.p: Notebook binder containing a handwritten textual draft along with notes on coins grouped into categories. The text is an introduction to a general work on the mint attributions for coins bearing the name and types of Alexander the Great. The notebook has the label "Amphipolis" on the cover, which may refer just to the section on specific coins, while the introductory text was intended for the broader work.
